# USB gadget serial console — read the mainline boot log over the usb/dp port
# WITHOUT the physical ttyS0 UART pads (no teardown / soldering).
#
# Merge this ON TOP of trimui.config for a BRING-UP kernel:
#   ./scripts/kconfig/merge_config.sh -m .config kernel/trimui.config kernel/usb-gadget-console.config
# and add to the kernel cmdline (belt-and-suspenders — both consoles get output):
#   console=ttyS0,115200 console=ttyGS0,115200
#
# The device then enumerates on the host as /dev/ttyACM0 (CDC-ACM, no host driver)
# or /dev/ttyUSB0 (generic). Read it with `usb-console.sh`, a WebSerial page, or any
# terminal. The usb/dp port must be in peripheral/gadget mode (plugging into the
# host PC makes MUSB peripheral; for certainty set the OTG node dr_mode="peripheral"
# on the bring-up DTB, overriding the role-switch).
#
# CAVEAT: the gadget console exists only from USB-gadget init onward — it does NOT
# capture SPL / U-Boot proper / the earliest pre-USB kernel lines. Validate DRAM in
# the FEL step serial-free with `sunxi-fel` memory read/write (see HARDWARE-BRINGUP.md).
#
# This is a SEPARATE bring-up fragment, not folded into trimui.config, because
# dedicating the usb/dp port to a gadget console conflicts with using it for host
# adapters / the USB-C role-switch in daily use. Drop it once serial isn't needed.
#
# NB: symbol names verified against the mainline gadget stack; re-confirm on the next
# build (merge_config silently drops any that don't apply).
CONFIG_USB_GADGET=y
CONFIG_USB_MUSB_HDRC=y
CONFIG_USB_MUSB_SUNXI=y
CONFIG_USB_MUSB_DUAL_ROLE=y
CONFIG_USB_LIBCOMPOSITE=y
CONFIG_USB_U_SERIAL=y
CONFIG_USB_G_SERIAL=y
CONFIG_U_SERIAL_CONSOLE=y
